    "body": "The value of an immutable variable is (in general) a runtime value. You cannot generate code for statically-sized arrays whose length depends on a runtime value:\r\n```\r\ncontract c {\r\n  uint immutable x = block.timestamp;\r\n  uint[x] data;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs it really a runtime variable for you or can you just as well use `constant`?",
